%N A396863 Discriminants of real quadratic fields with nontrivial Pólya group.
%C A396863 The Pólya group Po(K) of a number field K is the subgroup of class group Cl(K) generated by {products of prime ideals of O_K with norm q : q prime powers}. For K being a quadratic field, it is clear that Po(K) is generated by prime ideals lying above each ramified prime, and Po(K) is an elementary abelian 2-group.
%C A396863 D = A003658(n) such that A396865(n) != 0.
%H A396863 Jianing Song, <a href="/A396863/b396863.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%H A396863 Jean-Luc Chabert, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jnt.2019.03.008">From Pólya fields to Pólya groups (I) Galois extensions</a>, Journal of Number Theory, 2019, 203, pp.360-375.
%o A396863 (PARI) isA396863(D) = isfundamental(D) && D>1 && !(D==8 || isprime(D) || (omega(D)==2 && norm(quadunit(D))==1))
%Y A396863 Cf. A003658, A396865. A396862 is the complement with respect to A003658.
%K A396863 nonn
%O A396863 1,1
